OVERVIEW: Remove a group and its contents from the project

Removes a group and all its contents from the Xcode project.

Warning: This removes the group and all its contents from the project.

Examples:
  xcodeproj-cli remove-group Sources/Models
  xcodeproj-cli remove-group Utils

USAGE: xcodeproj-cli remove-group [--project <project>] [--workspace <workspace>] [--verbose] [--dry-run] <group-path>

ARGUMENTS:
  <group-path>            Path to the group to remove

OPTIONS:
  -p, --project <project> Path to .xcodeproj file (default: looks for
                          *.xcodeproj in current directory)
  -w, --workspace <workspace>
                          Path to .xcworkspace file
  -V, --verbose           Enable verbose output with performance metrics
  --dry-run               Preview changes without saving
  --version               Show the version.
  -h, --help              Show help information.

